0.1.1
=====

* SM2: Performance optimization
  - Refactor U256 type to use int array for better performance
  - Optimize arithmetic operations

* ZUC: Code consistency improvements
  - Optimize add31 and sbox_word functions to use Int32

0.1.0
=====

Initial release. Pure OCaml implementation of Chinese national cryptographic
algorithms:

* SM2: Public key cryptographic algorithm
  - Key derivation (public/private key generation)
  - Signature and verification (sign_digest, verify_digest)
  - Encryption and decryption
  - Key exchange protocol
  - DER/PEM/ASN.1 encoding and decoding
  - Encrypted private key PEM format support

* SM3: Hash algorithm
  - digest and digest_hex functions for string and hex input

* SM4: Block cipher
  - Single-block encryption/decryption
  - CBC mode with PKCS7 padding
  - CTR mode
  - GCM mode
  - Streaming context API (Ctr module for incremental encryption)

* ZUC-128: Stream cipher
  - Keystream generation
  - Stream encryption/decryption